hat any attempt to combat climate change requires a strategy to address coal morse argued that existing climate policy frameworks are not accomplishing this at the scale required and suggested new frameworks to address the coal and climate challenge that can be deployed in existing energy markets with limited government intervention and support downloads video video richard morse's talk and q&a session streaming flash video location university of texas welch hall 2.308 topics climate change coal energy search events everything events of interest india and climate change varun rai pdf+ hubbert's peak the coal question and climate change dave rutledge support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 1714 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
